3:
Yahweh, do not allow me to say things that are wrong;
\q2 guard what I say as a sentry guards a door.
\q1

5:
It is all right if righteous people strike me or rebuke me
\q2 because they are trying to act kindly toward me to teach me to do what is right;
\q1 if they do that, it will be as if someone honored me by anointing my head with olive oil;
\q2 but I am always praying that you will punish the wicked because of the wicked deeds that they do.
\b
\q1

9:
It is as though people have set traps for me;
\q2 protect me from falling into those traps.
\q2 It is as though they have spread nets to catch me;
\q2 keep me from being caught in those nets.
\q1
